```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) |> replace => '-' => '_'
end
```

This function uses the pipe operator (`|>`) to chain several operations on the input string `col`. First, it lowers the case using `lowercase()`, then strips leading and trailing whitespace with `strip()`. Finally, it replaces any hyphens (`-`) with underscores (`_`) using `replace(col, '-' => '_')`.

To test this function:

```julia
using Test

@testset "clean_column" begin
    @test clean_column("My Column") == "my_column"
    @test clean_column("my column") == "my_column"
    @test clean_column("my-column") == "my_column"
    @test clean_column("  my column   ") == "my_column"
end
```

This test suite ensures that the function works as expected for various input strings.
